    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-08-13T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-08-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="462"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d462">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Baron <persName type="from">Fava</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Adee</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Translation.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Italian Embassy</hi>
                        </placeName>,<lb/>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-08-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">August 13, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>My Government telegraphs me to ascertain the views of the Federal Government
                    concerning the telegrams sent to their respective Governments by the ministers
                    at Pekin, and how the Japanese proposition of an armistice for the release of
                    the legations was received by the United States. I beg you to write me very
                    courteously this evening on the subject, so as to enable me to answer without
                    delay. Thanks.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Fava.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
